flowRoot.flowPara: This certificate is valid only when and while:
a) It is being displayed accompanying a single instance of the work named in this certificate in the same single physical or virtual location,and;

b) This display has been organized by, or with the full knowledge and authorization of, either;c i.) The party controlling the private key of the Externally Owned Account for the address that is currently the ownerOf() the ERC-721 token with this image as its image URI metadata, or;c ii.) A multisig signature, vote, successful bid, or other valid exercise of governance authority by the smart contract or contracts that are currently the ownerOf() the ERC-721 token with this image as its image URI metadata, or;c iii.) An equivalent or successor singular expression of ownership and authority of this image - for example the beneficiary of a token rental or a cross-chain transfer but not a fractionalized wrapper token or copy of the image URI into another contract by an unauthorized third party.

text.tspan: This certificate is valid only when:
a) It is displayed accompanying a single instance of the work named above that is being displayed in the same physical or virtual location as this certificate, and;
b) This display has been organized by, or with the full knowledge and authorization of, either;
b i.) The party controlling the private key of the Externally Owned Account that is currently the ownerOf() the ERC-721 token with this image as its image URI metadata, or;

b ii.) The parties controlling the smart contract or contracts that are currently the ownerOf() the ERC-721 token with this image as its image URI metadata and can demosntrate sufficient authority to authorize this display using an appropriate on-chain mechanism, or;

b iii.) The party or parties able to establish equivalent or successor ownership of this image - for example the beneficiary of a token rental or of a cross-chain transfer but not the owner of a fractionalized wrapper token or copy of the image URI into another contract by a third party that has not been authorized to do so by the artist.
